{"stat": "ok", "comments": {"comment": [{"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633410923050", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "11418107@N02", "iconserver": "1068", "datecreate": "1367600370", "_content": "PROBABLY NOT Luis G. Peredo, &quot;a journalist during the Mexican Revolution, and became a pioneer in Mexican cinema&quot; (see below):\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melchor_Peredo\" rel=\"nofollow\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melchor_Peredo</a>", "authorname": "pennylrichardsca (now at ipernity)", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633410923050", "iconfarm": 2}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633395896599", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "66311327@N05", "iconserver": "7333", "datecreate": "1367605136", "_content": "I doubt that it's this Luis Peredo. Wikipedia says that the father of Melchor Peredo was Luis G. Peredo. \n\nAccording to <a href=\"http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030272/1915-10-20/ed-1/seq-14/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The sun, October 20, 1915, Page 14</a>, this is Luis A. Peredo, the first secretary of the Mexican Embassy (while Eliseo Arredondo was Carranza's personal representative in Washington, see photographs). He was previously engaged in the business of a commission broker. \n\nEliseo Arredondo: \n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883626/\" title=\"Eliseo Arredondo  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8546/8704883626_4414e23f55_m.jpg\" width=\"176\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Eliseo Arredondo  (LOC)\" /></a>", "authorname": "B-59", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633395896599", "iconfarm": 8}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633396026595", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "66311327@N05", "iconserver": "7333", "datecreate": "1367606478", "_content": "See also a photo of him in <a href=\"http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85058396/1914-06-15/ed-1/seq-1/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Ogden standard, June 15, 1914, 4 P.M. City Edition, page 1</a> &quot;REPRESENT CARRANZA AT WASHINGTON&quot;", "authorname": "B-59", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633396026595", "iconfarm": 8}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633396874561", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "11418107@N02", "iconserver": "1068", "datecreate": "1367615069", "_content": "[http://www.flickr.com/photos/66311327@N05] Much better candidate!  I'll amend above.", "authorname": "pennylrichardsca (now at ipernity)", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633396874561", "iconfarm": 2}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633413530726", "realname": "Art Siegel", "path_alias": "artolog", "author": "76016463@N00", "iconserver": "3807", "datecreate": "1367630142", "_content": "seems to be cropped from:<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883626/\" title=\"Eliseo Arredondo  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8546/8704883626_4414e23f55_m.jpg\" width=\"176\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Eliseo Arredondo  (LOC)\" /></a>", "authorname": "artolog", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633413530726", "iconfarm": 4}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633427296545", "realname": "Arden", "path_alias": "arden_loc", "author": "35072786@N08", "iconserver": "3331", "datecreate": "1367950625", "_content": "Thanks B-59 for finding the other images of Luis Peredo, secretary of the Mexican Embassy.  It does seem to be the same person.  I found some other images of him in P&amp;P's Harris &amp; Ewing collection: <a href=\"http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/hec.04285\" rel=\"nofollow\">hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/hec.04285</a>\nWe will update the description with more details.", "authorname": "Arden (LOC P&P)", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633427296545", "iconfarm": 4}, {"permalink": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8704883478/#comment72157633503496945", "realname": "", "path_alias": null, "author": "66311327@N05", "iconserver": "7333", "datecreate": "1368815634", "_content": "Cropped from\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/8747716000/\" title=\"Riccardo Vasquez, Luis D'Antin, Oscar E. Duplin, Francisco Paredo  (LOC) by The Library of Congress, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8416/8747716000_efba72806b_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"174\" alt=\"Riccardo Vasquez, Luis D'Antin, Oscar E. Duplin, Francisco Paredo  (LOC)\" /></a>", "authorname": "B-59", "id": "8602872-8704883478-72157633503496945", "iconfarm": 8}], "photo_id": "8704883478"}}